@Node "Intro" "Introduction to ModemActivator." 

                            @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

ModemActivator [from now on, MA] is a super small commodity coded in %100
assembler.

MA monitors your modem. When you turn on your modem, MA will detect your
modem, and start a program/script selected by the you!

MA checks to see if your modem has been turned on every user given
interval [in seconds]. So, it won't disturb your system in any way!!
If MA can't open your modem.device [eg. serial.device], it will just try
again in 'x' seconds!

When you have finished using your modem, and turn the modem off, MA will
detect this too!! Now it will wait for your modem to turn on again!!
You can change the check interval to your desire!

It is possible for MA to execute any kind of scripts/executeables.
Default stacksize has been set to 32 KB. If you wan't it increased, 
@{"contact " link "contact"} me, and I will change it to the size you require!


@EndNode

